title: Bug 49235: ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method returns unexpected class
description: The ServletContainerInitializer onStartup method returns 'MySomeClass' instead of the expected class.
EB: The expected class should be returned, but instead 'MySomeClass' is being returned.
SR:
1. Set up a project with a ServletContainerInitializer implementation.
2. In the onStartup method, call the getClasses() method on the provided ServletContext and store the result in a variable.
3. Print the value of the variable.
4. Run the project.
5. Check the output.
